where **Route number**=&lt;route ID&gt;."},{"content":"In other words, these operational properties apply when there is no operation relation for this route that is specific to either the released product or its associated item group.","pos":[12029,12208]},{"content":"All","pos":[12213,12216]},{"content":"All","pos":[12249,12252]},{"content":"The default operational properties of an operation.","pos":[12281,12332]},{"content":"These operational properties apply when a more specific operation relation doesn't exist.","pos":[12333,12422]},{"content":"You can also specify that an operation relation is specific to a site.","pos":[12585,12655]},{"content":"In this way, the operational properties of an operation can vary, depending on the location (that is, the site) where the operation is performed.","pos":[12656,12801]},{"content":"For configured products, you can also specify different operational properties for each product configuration.","pos":[12802,12912]},{"content":"Operation relations give you lots of flexibility when you define your routes.","pos":[12916,12993]},{"content":"Additionally, the ability to define default properties helps reduce the amount of master data that you must maintain.","pos":[12994,13111]},{"content":"However, this flexibility also means that you must be aware of the context that you modify an operation relation in.","pos":[13112,13228]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Because the operational properties are stored in operation relations per operation per route, all occurrences of the same operation (for example, Assembly) have the same setup time, run time, resource requirements, and so on.","pos":[13232,13467],"source":"**Note:** Because the operational properties are stored in operation relations per operation per route, all occurrences of the same operation (for example, Assembly) have the same setup time, run time, resource requirements, and so on."},{"content":"Therefore, if two occurrences of an operation must occur in the same route but have different run times, you must create two distinct operations, such as Assembly1 and Assembly2.","pos":[13468,13646]},{"pos":[13652,13685],"content":"Modifying product-specific routes","linkify":"Modifying product-specific routes","nodes":[{"content":"Modifying product-specific routes","pos":[0,33]}]},{"content":"When you open the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page from the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Released product details<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page, the route versions that are associated with the selected released product are shown.","pos":[13687,13848],"source":"When you open the **Route** page from the **Released product details** page, the route versions that are associated with the selected released product are shown."},{"content":"In this context, for each operation, Finance and Operations shows the operational properties from the operation relation that best matches the route version.","pos":[13849,14006]},{"content":"You will notice that the list of operations includes the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Item code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Route code<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> properties from the operation relation.","pos":[14007,14136],"source":" You will notice that the list of operations includes the **Item code** and **Route code** properties from the operation relation."},{"content":"Therefore, you can determine which operation relation is shown.","pos":[14137,14200]},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, you can modify the operational properties of the operation, such as the run time or the cost categories.","pos":[14204,14331],"source":"On the **Route** page, you can modify the operational properties of the operation, such as the run time or the cost categories."},{"content":"Your changes are stored on the operation relation that is specific to the route and released product that are referenced in the current route version.","pos":[14332,14482]},{"content":"If the operation relation that is shown isn't specific to the route and the released product, before your changes are stored, the system creates a copy of the operation relation.","pos":[14483,14661]},{"content":"This copy <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>is<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> specific to the route and released product.","pos":[14662,14720],"source":" This copy *is* specific to the route and released product."},{"content":"Therefore, your changes won't affect other routes or released products.","pos":[14721,14792]},{"content":"To verify which operation relation is being modified on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, look at the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Item code<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Route code<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> fields.","pos":[14793,14921],"source":" To verify which operation relation is being modified on the **Route** page, look at the **Item code** and **Route code** fields."},{"pos":[14925,15065],"content":"You can also manually create an operation that is specific to a route and released product by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Copy and edit relation<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function.","source":"You can also manually create an operation that is specific to a route and released product by using the **Copy and edit relation** function."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> If you add a new operation to a route on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page, an operation relation is created only for the current released product.","pos":[15069,15211],"source":"**Note:** If you add a new operation to a route on the **Route** page, an operation relation is created only for the current released product."},{"content":"Therefore, if the route is also used to produce other released products, no applicable operation relation will exist for those released products, and the route can no longer be used for those released products.","pos":[15212,15422]},{"pos":[15428,15469],"content":"Maintaining operation relations per route","linkify":"Maintaining operation relations per route","nodes":[{"content":"Maintaining operation relations per route","pos":[0,41]}]},{"content":"When you open the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route details<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page from the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Routes<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> list page, a list of all the operation relations that apply to the selected route is shown.","pos":[15471,15623],"source":"When you open the **Route details** page from the **Routes** list page, a list of all the operation relations that apply to the selected route is shown."},{"content":"Therefore, you can easily verify which operational properties are used for which products.","pos":[15624,15714]},{"content":"You can modify both default property values and product-specific property values.","pos":[15715,15796]},{"pos":[15800,16008],"content":"If you add a new operation relation on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route details<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Route code<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> field is automatically set to <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, and the <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Route relation<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> field is set to the route number of the current route.","source":"If you add a new operation relation on the **Route details** page, the **Route code** field is automatically set to **Route**, and the **Route relation** field is set to the route number of the current route."},{"pos":[16014,16059],"content":"Maintaining operation relations per operation","linkify":"Maintaining operation relations per operation","nodes":[{"content":"Maintaining operation relations per operation","pos":[0,45]}]},{"content":"From the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Operations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, you can open the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Operation relations<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page.","pos":[16061,16137],"source":"From the **Operations** page, you can open the **Operation relations** page."},{"content":"On this page, you can modify all operation relations for a specific operation.","pos":[16138,16216]},{"content":"You can even modify operation relations that contain default values.","pos":[16217,16285]},{"pos":[16289,16540],"content":"If your business uses standard operations, and if the operational parameters are the same across all products and processes, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Operation relations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page provides a convenient way to maintain the default operational properties of those operations.","source":"If your business uses standard operations, and if the operational parameters are the same across all products and processes, the **Operation relations** page provides a convenient way to maintain the default operational properties of those operations."},{"pos":[16546,16574],"content":"Applying operation relations","linkify":"Applying operation relations","nodes":[{"content":"Applying operation relations","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"In some cases, Finance and Operations must find the operational properties for an operation.","pos":[16576,16668]},{"content":"For example, when a purchase order is created, the operational properties of each operation must be copied from the operation relations to the production route.","pos":[16669,16829]},{"content":"In these situations, Finance and Operations searches the relevant operation relations from the most specific combination to the least specific combination.","pos":[16830,16985]},{"content":"When Finance and Operations searches for the most relevant operation relation for a released product, an operation relation that matches the item ID of the released product is preferred over an operation relation that matches the item group ID.","pos":[16989,17233]},{"content":"In turn, an operation relation that matches the item group ID is preferred over the default operation relation.","pos":[17234,17345]},{"content":"The search is done in the following order:","pos":[17346,17388]},{"pos":[17394,17455],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Item code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Table<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Item relation<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\">=</ph><ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>item ID<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>","source":"**Item code**=**Table** and **Item relation**=&lt;item ID&gt;"},{"pos":[17460,17527],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Item code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Group<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Item relation<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\">=</ph><ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>item group ID<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>","source":"**Item code**=**Group** and **Item relation**=&lt;item group ID&gt;"},{"pos":[17532,17553],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Item code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>All<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>","source":"**Item code**=**All**"},{"pos":[17558,17622],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Route<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Route relation<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph2\">=</ph><ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>route ID<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>","source":"**Route code**=**Route** and **Route relation**=&lt;route ID&gt;"},{"pos":[17627,17649],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Route code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>All<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>","source":"**Route code**=**All**"},{"pos":[17654,17696],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;lt;</ph>configuration ID<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph>","source":"**Configuration**=&lt;configuration ID&gt;"},{"pos":[17701,17719],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph>","source":"**Configuration**="},{"pos":[17724,17748],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Site<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;lt;</ph>site ID<ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph>","source":"**Site**=&lt;site ID&gt;"},{"pos":[17753,17762],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Site<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">=</ph>","source":"**Site**="},{"content":"Therefore, an operation should be used only one time for each route.","pos":[17764,17832]},{"content":"If the operation occurs multiple times in the same route, all occurrences of that operation will have the same operation relation, and you won't be able to have different properties (for example, run times) for each occurrence.","pos":[17833,18060]},{"pos":[18065,18079],"content":"Route versions","linkify":"Route versions","nodes":[{"content":"Route versions","pos":[0,14]}]},{"content":"Route versions are used to accommodate variations in the production of products or provide greater control over the production process.","pos":[18080,18215]},{"content":"They define which route should be used when a specific released product or released product variant is produced.","pos":[18216,18328]},{"content":"You can use the following constraints to define which route is used for a released product:","pos":[18329,18420]},{"content":"Product dimensions (size, color, style, or configuration)","pos":[18426,18483]},{"content":"Production quantity","pos":[18488,18507]},{"content":"Production site","pos":[18512,18527]},{"content":"Production date","pos":[18532,18547]},{"content":"When you're producing the product at a specific site, in a specific quantity, or in a specific period, you can designate a specific route version as the default route version.","pos":[18549,18724]},{"content":"However, note that only one active route is allowed for a given released product and a given set of constraints.","pos":[18725,18837]},{"content":"In the Production control parameters, you can require that the validity period of a route version always be specified.","pos":[18841,18959]},{"pos":[18965,18991],"content":"Approval of route versions","linkify":"Approval of route versions","nodes":[{"content":"Approval of route versions","pos":[0,26]}]},{"content":"Before a route version can be used in the planning or manufacturing process, it must be approved.","pos":[18993,19090]},{"content":"When you approve a route version, you can also approve the related route.","pos":[19091,19164]},{"content":"However, note that a route version can be approved only if the related route is also approved.","pos":[19165,19259]},{"pos":[19265,19301],"content":"Activating the default route version","linkify":"Activating the default route version","nodes":[{"content":"Activating the default route version","pos":[0,36]}]},{"content":"When you activate a route version, you designate it as the default route version that master planning will use, or that will be used to create production orders.","pos":[19303,19464]},{"content":"You can have only one active route version for a given set of constraints (for example, period, site, or quantity).","pos":[19465,19580]},{"content":"If the version that you’re trying to activate conflicts with a version that is already active, you receive an error message.","pos":[19581,19705]},{"content":"To prevent an ambiguous activation, you must then either inactivate the conflicting version or modify the constraints (usually the period) on the route version.","pos":[19706,19866]},{"pos":[19872,19893],"content":"Electronic signatures","linkify":"Electronic signatures","nodes":[{"content":"Electronic signatures","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"If you must keep a log that records who approves and activates each route version, you can require electronic signatures for these tasks.","pos":[19895,20032]},{"content":"Users who approve and activate route versions will then have to confirm their identity by using an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>electronic signature<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/fin-and-ops/organization-administration/electronic-signature-overview)</ept>.","pos":[20033,20258],"source":" Users who approve and activate route versions will then have to confirm their identity by using an [electronic signature](/dynamics365/unified-operations/fin-and-ops/organization-administration/electronic-signature-overview)."},{"pos":[20264,20304],"content":"Product change that uses case management","linkify":"Product change that uses case management","nodes":[{"content":"Product change that uses case management","pos":[0,40]}]},{"content":"The product change case for the approval and activation of new or changed routes and route versions gives you an easy way to see an overview of the route version constraints.","pos":[20306,20480]},{"content":"You can also approve and activate all routes that are related to a specific change in one operation and document the results in the product change case.","pos":[20481,20633]},{"pos":[20638,20656],"content":"Maintaining routes","linkify":"Maintaining routes","nodes":[{"content":"Maintaining routes","pos":[0,18]}]},{"content":"Depending on your business requirements, you might be able to reduce the effort that is required in order to maintain your process definitions.","pos":[20657,20800]},{"pos":[20806,20844],"content":"Making routes independent of resources","linkify":"Making routes independent of resources","nodes":[{"content":"Making routes independent of resources","pos":[0,38]}]},{"content":"In many systems, the operations resource or resource group that should perform an operation must be specified in the route.","pos":[20846,20969]},{"content":"However, in Finance and Operations, you can define a set of requirements that an operations resource must meet to be applicable for the operation.","pos":[20970,21116]},{"content":"Therefore, the specific operations resource or resource group that should be used doesn't have to be determined until the operation is actually scheduled.","pos":[21117,21271]},{"content":"This functionality is especially useful when you have many workers or machines that can perform the same operation.","pos":[21272,21387]},{"content":"For example, you specify that an operation requires an operations resource of the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Machine<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> type that has a <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Stamping<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> capability of 20 tons.","pos":[21391,21536],"source":"For example, you specify that an operation requires an operations resource of the **Machine** type that has a **Stamping** capability of 20 tons."},{"content":"The scheduling engine will then resolve these requirements to a specific operations resource or resource group when the operation is scheduled.","pos":[21537,21680]},{"content":"Because you can just specify these requirements instead of binding the operation to a specific machine, you have much more flexibility.","pos":[21681,21816]},{"content":"Additionally, maintenance is easier when resources are moved or new resources are added.","pos":[21817,21905]},{"pos":[21909,22091],"content":"For more information about the various types of resource requirements and how to use them, see Operations resource requirements and <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Resource capabilities<ept id=\"p1\">](resource-capabilities.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information about the various types of resource requirements and how to use them, see Operations resource requirements and [Resource capabilities](resource-capabilities.md)."},{"pos":[22097,22124],"content":"Sharing routes across sites","linkify":"Sharing routes across sites","nodes":[{"content":"Sharing routes across sites","pos":[0,27]}]},{"content":"If you produce the same product at more than one production site, and if the steps for producing the product are the same at all sites, you can often design a shared route that is used across all production sites.","pos":[22126,22339]},{"content":"To create a shared route, don't specify a site on the route itself.","pos":[22340,22407]},{"content":"However, you must still create a route version that associates the shared route with the product at each site.","pos":[22408,22518]},{"content":"You must also make sure that the resource requirements for each operation in the route don't call for specific operations resources or resource groups, but are instead expressed in terms of the characteristics of the required resources.","pos":[22522,22758]},{"content":"The scheduling engine will then be able to assign the appropriate operations resources from the site that the production is scheduled on.","pos":[22759,22896]},{"content":"For example, if there are small differences in the run time, or if the setup time for a certain operation is site-specific, you can specify this information by adding an additional operation relation for that site.","pos":[22897,23111]},{"content":"To take full advantage of the benefits of shared routes, you should also use resource consumption on the corresponding bill of materials (BOM).","pos":[23115,23258]},{"content":"When you set the flag for resource consumption on the BOM line, the warehouse and location that raw materials should be consumed from is inferred from the operations resource that the operation is scheduled on.","pos":[23259,23469]},{"content":"Therefore, the warehouse and location don't have to be determined until the production is actually scheduled.","pos":[23470,23579]},{"content":"In this way, you can make both the BOM and the route independent of the physical location where the product is produced.","pos":[23580,23700]},{"pos":[23706,23734],"content":"Standard operation relations","linkify":"Standard operation relations","nodes":[{"content":"Standard operation relations","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"If your business uses standardized operations throughout production, and if there is little or no variation in the setup time, run time, consumption calculation, cost calculation, and so on, you might benefit from creating default operation relations for all operations.","pos":[23736,24006]},{"content":"In this case, avoid creating operation relations that are specific to any route or released product.","pos":[24007,24107]},{"content":"If you also express resource requirements in terms of skills and capabilities, and make your routes site-independent, you can help keep the ongoing maintenance of your business processes to a minimum.","pos":[24111,24311]},{"pos":[24315,24456],"content":"When you use this approach, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Operation relations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page becomes your primary destination for maintaining run times and other properties.","source":"When you use this approach, the **Operation relations** page becomes your primary destination for maintaining run times and other properties."},{"pos":[24462,24493],"content":"Resource-specific process times","linkify":"Resource-specific process times","nodes":[{"content":"Resource-specific process times","pos":[0,31]}]},{"content":"If you don't specify an operations resource or resource group as part of the resource requirements for an operation, the applicable resources might operate at different speeds.","pos":[24495,24671]},{"content":"Therefore, the time that is required in order to process an operation might vary.","pos":[24672,24753]},{"content":"To resolve this issue, you can use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Formula<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field on the operation relation to specify how the process time is calculated.","pos":[24754,24883],"source":" To resolve this issue, you can use the **Formula** field on the operation relation to specify how the process time is calculated."},{"content":"The following options are available:","pos":[24884,24920]},{"pos":[24926,25083],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Standard<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – (Default option) The calculation uses only the fields from the operation relation and multiplies the specified run time by the order quantity.","source":"**Standard** – (Default option) The calculation uses only the fields from the operation relation and multiplies the specified run time by the order quantity."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Capacity<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – The calculation includes the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Capacity<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> field from the operations resource.","pos":[25088,25180],"source":"**Capacity** – The calculation includes the **Capacity** field from the operations resource."},{"content":"Therefore, the time is resource-dependent.","pos":[25181,25223]},{"content":"The value that is specified on the operations resource is capacity per hour.","pos":[25224,25300]},{"content":"This value is multiplied by the order quantity and the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Factor<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> value from the operation relation.","pos":[25301,25401],"source":" This value is multiplied by the order quantity and the **Factor** value from the operation relation."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Batch<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – A batch capacity is calculated by using information from the operation relation.","pos":[25406,25498],"source":"**Batch** – A batch capacity is calculated by using information from the operation relation."},{"content":"The number of batches and, therefore, the process time can then be calculated based on the order quantity.","pos":[25499,25605]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Resource batch<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This option is basically the same as the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Batch<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> option.","pos":[25610,25689],"source":"**Resource batch** – This option is basically the same as the **Batch** option."},{"content":"However, the calculation includes the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Batch capacity<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field from the operations resource.","pos":[25690,25782],"source":" However, the calculation includes the **Batch capacity** field from the operations resource."},{"content":"Therefore, the time is resource-dependent.","pos":[25783,25825]},{"pos":[25828,25836],"content":"See also","linkify":"See also","nodes":[{"content":"See also","pos":[0,8]}]},{"pos":[25847,25905],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Bills of materials and formulas<ept id=\"p1\">](bill-of-material-bom.md)</ept>","source":"[Bills of materials and formulas](bill-of-material-bom.md)"},{"pos":[25907,26015],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Cost categories used in production routing<ept id=\"p1\">](../cost-management/cost-categories-used-production-routings.md)</ept>","source":"[Cost categories used in production routing](../cost-management/cost-categories-used-production-routings.md)"},{"pos":[26017,26066],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Resource capabilities<ept id=\"p1\">](resource-capabilities.md)</ept>","source":"[Resource capabilities](resource-capabilities.md)"},{"pos":[26068,26202],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Electronic signature overview<ept id=\"p1\">](/dynamics365/unified-operations/fin-and-ops/organization-administration/electronic-signature-overview)</ept>","source":"[Electronic signature overview](/dynamics365/unified-operations/fin-and-ops/organization-administration/electronic-signature-overview)"}]}